code: /**  * Creates a new tuple and assigns the given values to the tuple's fields.  * This is more convenient than using the constructor, because the compiler can  * infer the generic type arguments implicitly. For example:  * {@code Tuple3.of(n, x, s)}  * instead of  * {@code new Tuple3<Integer, Double, String>(n, x, s)}  */ public static <T0, T1, T2> Tuple3<T0, T1, T2> of(T0 value0, T1 value1, T2 value2) {     return new Tuple3<>(value0, value1, value2). }
